'''Point Comfort''' is a historic house on South Skakutakee Road in [[Harrisville, New Hampshire]].  Built in 1892, this 2-1/2 story wood frame house is one of the earliest summer resort houses to be built along the shores of [[Silver Lake (Harrisville, New Hampshire)|Silver Lake]].  It is eclectically styled, with steeply pitched gables, bands of shingles on the walls, exposed rafter ends, and decorative rake boards.<ref name=NRHP>{{cite web|url={{NRHP url|id=86003256}}|title=NRHP nomination for Point Comfort|publisher=National Park Service|accessdate=2014-04-25}}</ref>

The house was listed on the [[National Register of Historic Places]] in 1988.<ref name="nris"/>

